This is used to exit from the method and optionally returns a value. 

Syntax:

for(initialization; condition; inc/dec) {
  if(condition) {
    return; (or) return value;
  }
}

int []nums = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8};

for(int num: nums) {
  if(num == 4) {
    return; // in case of void method
  }
  System.out.println(num);
}

output: 1, 2, 3


int num1 = 2;
int num2 = 3;

int output = add(num1, num2);

System.out.println(output);

int add(int num1, int num2) {
  return num1 + num2;
}

output: 5;